You can't do that. The message ID is set when the message is sent and cannot be changed, so the notifications for it also contain ID "message-xxxxxxxxx-x".
Trimming the ID will break your system.

If you want to get rid of the prefixes you can change line 1389 in whatsprot.class.php from
```php
protected function createMsgId($prefix)
    {
        $msgid = "$prefix-" . time() . '-' . $this->messageCounter;
        $this->messageCounter++;

        return $msgid;
    }
```
to
```php
protected function createMsgId()
    {
        $msgid = time() . '-' . $this->messageCounter;
        $this->messageCounter++;

        return $msgid;
    }
```
https://github.com/venomous0x/WhatsAPI/blob/master/src/php/whatsprot.class.php#L1389

PS
just using $node->getData() is a bad idea as it does not always contain a text message. This node may as well be a media node (e.g. when you send a picture or a sound clip)
Make sure to check the node tag first:
```php
if($node->getTag() == "body")
{
    $text = $node->getData();
    ...
}
```
